CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 6, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Young Artists - Appearing the last musicale salon given each month by Marie Carter Hayes were these young artists, who performed before a capacity audience.  Young Yvonne Gibson was the piano soloist and William Brown, accompanied by William Bretz, was the young man who astounded the audience with his singing. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Yvonne Gibson at piano and vocalist William Brown standing beside her, in Hayes School of Music, 6490 Frankstown Avenue, East Liberty, vertical format
